iv class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-afc4cee unicamp-accordion-style-01 elementor-widget elementor-widget-tm-accordion\" data-id=\"afc4cee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;active_first_item&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"tm-accordion.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"unicamp-accordion unicamp-accordion-icon-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section active\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Justice (Rtd.) Charles A. Nyachae - Chairperson<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-icons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon opened-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-down\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon closed-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-up\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10635 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-768x1152.jpg 768w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-22-scaled.jpg 1707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" \/><\/strong>Judge Rtd. Nyachae is a top legal mind with a successful career spanning many years. Before his appointment to serve at the helm of the School, he was Judge of the Arusha-based East African Court of Justice from 2018 to 2024, a cross-border body for the East African Community that is instrumental in the settlement of disputes amongst member states and contributing to harmonization of laws in partner states through the development of jurisprudence in the regions.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Previously, he was the first and the only Chairperson of the one and only Commission for the Implementation of the Constitution (CIC) from 2010 to 2015, a body established for midwifing and overseeing the transition into the new dispensation where he played a pivotal role in implementing the Constitution, entrenching the institutions created by the Constitution and safeguarding and promoting democracy in the country.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">As the Chair of the CIC, together with the other Commissioners, he steered the understanding of the letter and spirit of the Constitution and translated it into the various bills enacted by the Parliament to implement the Constitution.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">He is a member of several professional and peer organizations: the Law Society of Kenya, the East African Law Society, the Institute of Certified Public Secretaries (Kenya), the Chartered Institute of Arbitrators (UK), Chartered Institute of Chartered Mediators and Conciliators, International Bar Association and the Commonwealth Law Association.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Mr. Denis M. Mutahi - Member representing Principal Secretary, State Department for Public Service<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-icons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon opened-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-down\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon closed-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-up\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10636  alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"138\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-768x1152.jpg 768w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-17-scaled.jpg 1707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 138px) 100vw, 138px\" \/><\/strong><\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Mr. Mutahi holds a Master\u2019s of Science in Human Resource Planning and Development and a Bachelors of Education. He is career civil servant with over 20 years of civil service experience and currently serving as a Director of Human Resource Management and Development, State Department for Public Service. He is a member in the Human Resource Committee, Risk and audit, Learning and Development and Finance and General Purpose Committee.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Mr. Micah Origa - Member representing Principal Secretary, National Treasury<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-icons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon opened-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-down\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon closed-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-up\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10637  alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"161\" height=\"242\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13-768x1152.jpg 768w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/Portraits-13.jpg 1202w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 161px) 100vw, 161px\" \/><\/strong><\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Micah Origa holds a Master of Science Degree (MSC Finance) from the University of Nairobi, Master of Business Administration (MBA) and a Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) degree. He is also Certified Public Accountant (CPA- K).<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Mr. Origa has wide experience in public sector budget formulation, preparation, implementation and monitoring.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">He has sat on several other Boards over the last ten years. He is a member in the Audit and Risk as well as Finance and General Purpose committees.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div cl