<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">He is the Chairperson for Finance and General Purpose and a member in the Learning and Development committees respectively.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Dr. Rose Ngugi - Member representing KIPPRA<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-icons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon opened-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-down\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon closed-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-up\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-9739 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"245\" height=\"163\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43-300x200.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43-1024x684.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43-768x513.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43-1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43-600x401.jpeg 600w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-02-02-at-19.17.43.jpeg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 245px) 100vw, 245px\" \/><\/strong>Dr. Rose Ngugi is the Executive Director of the Kenya Institute for Public Policy Research and Analysis (KIPPRA). She is involved in providing technical guidance and capacity building on policy and strategy formulation to the Government of Kenya and other stakeholders, with the overall aim of contributing to the achievement of national development goals.<\/p><p>Before then, she was a Senior Advisor in the Office of Executive Director, Africa Group 1, International Monetary Fund, and Washington D.C. Dr. Ngugi has been a member of Central Bank of Kenya, Monetary Policy Committee and has vast teaching experience in the University of Nairobi, School of Economics.<\/p><p>Dr Ngugi has published widely. Her research interests are in public policy, financial sector, investments, reforms and institutional issues.<\/p><p>She holds a PhD from Business School Birmingham University, UK specializing in Financial Markets, a Masters and Bachelors degree in Economics from the University of Nairobi, Kenya.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left\">\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Ms. Gatwiri Kirimi - Indpendent Member<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-icons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon opened-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-down\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon closed-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-up\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10639  alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"153\" height=\"230\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-768x1152.jpg 768w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/portraits-scaled.jpg 1707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 153px) 100vw, 153px\" \/><\/strong>Ms. Gatwiri holds a Master\u2019s of International Business Administration, Strategic Management Entrepreneurship and a Bachelor of Science Degree (Marketing) from United States International University.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Currently she is a Managing Director at Inforparts Technologies Limited.<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">She is the Chairperson for the Human Resource Committee and a member of Finance and General Purpose Committee<\/p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Ms. Linnet Mirehane - Independent  Member<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-icons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon opened-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-down\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"accordion-icon closed-icon\"><i class=\"far fa-angle-up\"><\/i><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-5256 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/dev.xtranet.co.ke\/KSG2\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/linnet-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/linnet-199x300.jpg 199w, https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/linnet.jpg 207w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px\" \/>Ms. Linnet Mirehane currently serves as a Non-Executive Director of the National Bank of Kenya (NBK), a position she has held since 2015. During this period she has served as Chairperson of NBK Bancassurance Intermediary Limited, Chairperson of the Board Risk Committee, and a Member of Board Credit Committee. She has also served as the Chairperson of NBK Staff Pension Fund.<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Earlier, she worked with the Teachers Service Commission as a high school teacher. She is also a Trainer of Trainers in Leadership and a Certified Professional Mediator and has credible experience in designing, implementing, and managing of programs in areas of good governance, gender, human rights and democracy having worked with Civil Societies and educational institutions.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ms. Mirahane holds a Bachelor of Education from Kenyatta University and a Diploma in Management of Non-Governmental Organizations (NGO) from the Kenya Institute of Management.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">She has attended courses in finance, risk and Board affairs both locally and internationally, and is a member of the Institute of Directors, Insurance Institute of Kenya, Women on Boards Network, and Suluhu Mediation Centre.<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">She brings on board a wealth of experience from her corporate and public sector background as she joins the Council of Kenya School of Government as an Independent Member.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-header\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accordion-title-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"accordion-title\">Mr. Ezekiel Owuor - Independent  Member<\/h6>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"accor